    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="844"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.85/204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-23T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 23, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1302. Re sale of CSAV vessels to WSA. Chilean Senate yesterday considered
                    approval of proposed sale in secret sessions lasting all day. <pb facs="0895"
                        n="883" xml:id="pg_883"/> Upon adjourning it decided to resume consideration
                    on Monday July 26 and Tuesday July 27.</p>
                <p>What appears to be worrying the Senate is possibility that CSAV will use proceeds
                    of sale for other purposes and at end of war no funds will be available to
                    purchase replacement vessels. Senate is considering making its approval
                    conditional upon payment for vessels in gold bars to be brought to Chile for
                    safekeeping. I know Foreign Minister is amazed and distressed by Senate’s delay.
                    Vial confident of Senate approval Tuesday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
